g.text: Exercise 4: Table Restructuring
In this exercise you change data structure by unpivoting columns to rows.
Change the structure of the table with the onsite purchases so that each purchased product is in a separate row and not
the whole purchase event
Unpivot the columns that show the products ordered in one purchase event. Retain other columns in the table.
Remove rows that have missing values for the unpivoted column values
Rename "ColumnValues" column to "ProductNr" and "ShoppingNumber" to "OrderNumber"
Remove unnecessary columns "BasketSize" and "ColumnNames"
Hint: combine tasks 1.3 and 1.4 using a single Table Manipulator node
(optional) Format the product numbers
Split the product numbers into substrings where separated by "-"
Convert the middle part to string and padLeft with zeros to create a 3-char code
Combine the manipulated substrings back to one string, and replace the product numbers by these manipulated values
Read onsite
transactions data
